==Events== *February: [[Motion Picture Story|The Motion Picture Story Magazine]], the first American film [[fan magazine]], is published. It is followed later in the year by [[Photoplay]]. *March 23: [[D. W. Griffith]] shows the first major close-up shot on film with the successful release of ''[[The Lonedale Operator]]'' proving his ever-growing mastery of how to utilise film. *April 8: [[Winsor McCay]] releases his first film ''[[Little Nemo (1911 film)|Little Nemo]]'', one of the earliest animated films. *October 27: [[David Horsley]]'s [[Nestor Studios|Nestor Motion Picture Company]] opens the first motion picture studio in [[Hollywood]]. *''[[Defence of Sevastopol]]'' premiers at the palace of Tsar Nicholas II and becomes the first feature-length film made in the Russian Empire and one of the first in the world. *The [[Kalem Company]] of [[New York City|New York]] pays the estate of author [[Lew Wallace]] $25,000 in legal settlement for having adapted [[Ben Hur (1907 film)|''Ben Hur'' (1907 film)]] from [[Ben-Hur: A Tale of the Christ|his novel]] without securing prior rights.
