'''Manjot Kaur''' (born 1989) is a contemporary Indian artist, who lives and works in [[Chandigarh]].<ref name="Heart of the Matter">{{Cite news|url=http://epaper.indianexpress.com/1140966/Chandigarh/March-19,-2017#page/25/3|title=Heart of the Matter|date=2017-03-19|work=https://www.http://epaper.indianexpress.com.com/|language=en}}</ref>
== About == She completed her BFA and MFA ( University Gold Medal)<ref name="30 under 30" /> in the field of Painting from [[Government College of Arts, Chandigarh]], in 2010 and 2012 respectively. Her mediums range from drawing to video, interactive performance, land art and installation.<ref>{{cite news|title=For art's sake|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/life-style/for-art-s-sake/480250.html|accessdate=11 Oct 2017|agency=The Tribune}}</ref>
== Awards == She is recipient of Professional Category Annual Award, [[Punjab Lalit Kala Akademi]] (State Academy of Art), Chandigarh, India, 2018;<ref>{{cite news|title=Lalit Kala Akademi announces eight winners for its annual art exhibition|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/lalit-kala-akademi-announces-eight-winners-for-its-annual-art-exhibition/articleshow/63214312.cms|accessdate=8 March 2018|agency=Times of India|publisher=Times of India}}</ref> Sohan Qadri Fellowship, [[Chandigarh Lalit Kala Akademi ]](State Academy of Art), Chandigarh, India 2017;<ref>{{cite news|title=Manjot Kaur wins Sohan Qadri fellowship|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/manjot-kaur-wins-sohan-qadri-fellowship/story-92PCaFdI1Zg6dZnEC1HbVN.html|accessdate=9 Oct 2017|agency=Hindustan Times|publisher=Hindustan Times}}</ref> Professional and Student Category Annual Award, Chandigarh Lalit Kala Akademi (State Academy of Art), Chandigarh, India, 2017<ref>{{cite news|title=Painting Dreams : Laurels for professional and budding tricity artists|url=https://www.pressreader.com/india/hindustan-times-chandigarh-city/20170214/281887298061201|accessdate=14 Feb 2017|agency=Hindustan Times}}</ref> and 2012,<ref>{{cite news|title=Chandigarh Lalit Kala Akademi rewards artistic talent at Annual Art Exhibition 2012|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/events/chandigarh/Chandigarh-Lalit-Kala-Akademi-rewards-artistic-talent-at-Annual-Art-Exhibition-2012/articleshow/17965169.cms|accessdate=24 Mar 2014|agency=Times of India}}</ref> respectively and Scholarship to Young Artists, Chandigarh Lalit Kala Akademi (State Academy of Art), Chandigarh, India in 2011 <ref name="Heart of the Matter"/> . She was chosen by Hindustan Times as one of the Top 30 under 30 young achievers in 2017.<ref name="30 under 30">{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/ht-youth-forum-2017-manjot-kaur-among-top-30-under-30/story-wvBQXQTvfpluGa9rBloWyM.html|title=HT Youth Forum 2017: Manjot Kaur among Top 30 Under 30|date=2017-05-23|work=Hindustan Times|access-date=2018-04-16|language=en}}</ref>
